{"id":510978608,"lang":"java","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1624257879,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/510978608/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"N/A","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\n\n//They are already in reversed order!\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode dummy=new ListNode(0);\n        \n        ListNode l3=dummy;\n        int carry=0;\n        while(l1!=null && l2!=null)\n        {\n            int l1_value=(l1!=null)?l1.val:0;\n            \n            int l2_value=(l2!=null)?l2.val:0;\n            \n            \n            int currentSum=l1_value+l2_value+carry;\n            carry=currentSum/10;\n            int lastDigit=currentSum%10;\n            ListNode newNode=new ListNode(lastDigit);\n            l3.next=newNode;\n            if(l1!=null)l1=l1.next;\n            if(l2!=null);l2=l2.next;\n            \n            l3=l3.next;\n        }\n        \n        if(carry>0)\n        {\n            ListNode newNode=new ListNode(carry);\n            l3.next=newNode;\n            l3=l3.next;\n        }\n        \n        return dummy.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
